WHO Pilot Investigation of SARI
This table shows pilot data from the fisrt 10 reporting facilities. The World Health Organization (WHO) case definition of severe acute respiratory infections (SARI) is anyone with an acute respiratory infection with symptoms within 10 days of presentation, cough, fever, and hospitalization.
